    },
    "summary": {
      "rules": [
        "Hard adjectives: -ЫЙ/-ОЙ (m), -АЯ (f), -ОЕ (n), -ЫЕ (pl)",
        "Soft adjectives (after Г К Х Ж Ш Щ Ч): -ИЙ (m), -АЯ (f), -ЕЕ (n), -ИЕ (pl)",
        "Dictionary form = masculine nominative — always the starting point",
        "Possessives мой/наш/ваш also agree in gender and number"
      ],
      "vocabulary": ["новый", "большой", "красивый", "хороший", "маленький", "старый"],
      "nextLesson": "Next: adjective endings in cases — how новый becomes нового in genitive and новому in dative."
    }
